00Z","msg":"Dear all,<br />\n<br />\nGood morning.<br />\n<br />\nConcerning the sharing of Rev. Dr. Alvin Cheah which I forwarded to you, teammates, on 23/7 and the related petition against me among alumni, I would like to make a few points as clarification:<br />\n<br />\n* This WhatsApp group is in existence for sharing of school news and matters of concern.  The participation in the group is voluntary even though I had extended my invitation to all, mainly teachers.  I forwarded the writing of Rev. Dr. Alvin Cheah to the group after I received the message from one of you concerning the situation of HK on 23/7.<br />\n<br />\n* The sharing in the group was not intended to be a MASS MAIL as accused.<br />\n<br />\n* Rev. Cheah's article is not my writing, but one forwarded to me by an alumnus on 23/7, the same day.<br />\n<br />\n* My main concern at that time was that we should &quot;pray for the young people ... pray for peace ... May God save the precious young people of HK&quot;.<br />\n<br />\n* In fact different and diverse views have been circulated in the same group, e.g. one from Mr. Eric Cheung TM on 26/6 (after his talk to students &amp; teachers in Munsang College and upon his consent) and another one of Prof. 陳弘毅 (公開信) on 2/7.   These two are appended.<br />\n<br />\n* I find myself duty-bound to share various salient arguments of opposing sides to issues of importance to our community with colleagues.   As educators, I believe, we should always keep an open mind.<br />\n<br />\n* All in all, for healthy development of our community, I am against violence of all parties.<br />\n<br />\nPray that things in HK will be back to normal as soon as possible.<br />\n<br />\nBest regards from Macedonia, 9:00 am<br />\nKuby"},{"pid":"9148078cccf6b693ec44e53c69cf437517444c21","tid":1391928,"uid":285708,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"quote":{"pid":"f8cabc12690355b0ae9691b24b5026dbae55935e","tid":1391928,"uid":292242,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":3,"re